["Joel Dias Barcellos (27 November 1936 \u2013 10 November 2018[1]) was a Brazilian actor. He appeared in 53 films and television shows between 1955 and 1997. He starred in the 1974 film Sagarana: The Duel, which was entered into the 24th Berlin International Film Festival.[2] In 2012 it was reported that he died while swimming, but this later turned out to be false.[3][4]","This article about a Brazilian actor is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]